{
  "texts": [
    "While these are useful to many patients, these approaches may still suffer from the barriers of in-person attendance and constant clinical supervision (as discussed in the introduction section).",
    "A large number of the studies reviewed developed AI-driven VRehab platforms, however, they only tested them on healthy participants, clinicians, students, or research team members.",
    "Those studies were deemed out of scope for our review as we emphasize on improving health outcomes for patients living in the community using AI-driven VRehab solutions.",
    "Studies in which video games, virtual reality, or augmented reality were used to deliver VRehab without the application of AI methods were also excluded.",
    "In order to identify relevant studies, a comprehensive literature search was developed in collaboration with a Library Sciences Expert (M.P.)"
  ]
}